      "actionDate": "2026-02-24",
      "actionDesc": "Reported to House",
      "text": "<p><strong>National Emergency Medical Services Memorial Extension Act</strong></p><p>This bill reauthorizes the National Emergency Medical Services Memorial Foundation to establish&nbsp;in Washington, DC, a monument to commemorate the commitment and service represented by emergency medical services. This authorization expires seven years after enactment of the bill.</p>",
      "updateDate": "2026-03-12T14:12:13Z",
      "versionCode": "07"
